```
public interface Printable {
    // no methods
}
```

By doing so, any class that implements Printable will effectively inherit this interface's type and can be treated as printable by other parts of the code. For instance, we can create a Document class that implements Printable and use it in a print() method without caring about its internal implementation:

```
